  "title": "Drafter (Revit / AutoCAD) - ACMV",
  "description": "<p><strong>About the Role</strong></p><p>We are looking for a <strong>Drafter</strong> who is detail-oriented and passionate about producing accurate, high-quality drawings. You will work closely with Project Engineers and Project Managers to prepare and coordinate drawings from design through construction to as-built stage.<br /></p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong>     </p><ul><li>Prepare and update <strong>drawings and designdocuments</strong> for preliminary, construction, and as-built stages using <strong>BIM, AutoCAD, and Revit</strong>.Assist <strong>Project Engineers</strong> and <strong>Project Managers</strong> in drawing preparation and coordination.</li><li>Stay current with <strong>drafting and BIM technologies</strong> to maintain technical competency.</li><li>Plan and manage drawing submissions to meet deadlines.</li><li>Ensure timely delivery and maintain proper soft copy archives of all drawings. </li><li>Draft detailed installation and construction plans from sketches or notes.</li><li>Finalize and reproduce documentation packages according to project standards.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Diploma or Degree</strong> in Engineering, Architecture, or related discipline.</li><li>Experience managing <strong>multiple projects</strong> simultaneously.</li><li>Strong <strong>communication skills</strong> in English and/or Chinese.</li><li>Excellent <strong>organization and time management</strong> abilities.</li><li>Proficient in <strong>AutoCAD and Revit (BIM modelling), Navisworks, and Microsoft Office</strong>.</li><li>Able to work independently with accuracy and responsibility.</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Why Join Us</strong>      </p><ul><li>Exposure to diverse construction and <strong>M&E </strong>projects.</li><li>Supportive and professional <strong>team environment.</strong></li><li>Convenient workplace near <strong>Jurong East MRT / Toh Guan area</strong>.</li></ul>",
